1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:01,610
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,610 --> 00:00:03,540
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:05,180
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,510 --> 00:00:07,910
(Episode 53)

5
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:24,460
Who are you?

6
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:43,420
Anyway, what am I doing here?

7
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:46,850
Today's my college orientation.

8
00:00:49,390 --> 00:00:51,020
Did I get into an accident
on my way there?

9
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,890
What? College orientation day?

10
00:00:57,330 --> 00:00:58,400
Park Min Jun.

11
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,100
Min Jun.

12
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:30,090
Who are you?

13
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:38,870
What?

14
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:42,470
What are you trying to pull?

15
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:54,790
Chloe! Chloe, are you okay?

16
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:57,760
I hope you're all right.

17
00:02:01,690 --> 00:02:02,960
What on earth happened?

18
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:05,230
How did you end up
in an accident there?

19
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:09,730
Wait. Is my name Chloe?

20
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,840
What?

21
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,040
Who am I?

22
00:02:17,980 --> 00:02:20,350
I can't remember anything.

23
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,480
What?

24
00:02:25,650 --> 00:02:26,650
Chloe.

25
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:31,920
Hello.

26
00:02:32,990 --> 00:02:33,990
What?

27
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:36,560
Min Jun lost his memory?

28
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,920
You want updates
on Min Jun and Chloe...

29
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,780
at the same time?

30
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:03,860
Well, they were
in the same accident,

31
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:06,690
and I'm told they both have amnesia.

32
00:03:06,890 --> 00:03:10,460
I need to know
what's going on immediately.

33
00:03:10,730 --> 00:03:12,830
Yes, I agree.

34
00:03:13,130 --> 00:03:15,830
They both lost their memories.
What on earth is going on?

35
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:17,400
Please explain.

36
00:03:17,770 --> 00:03:20,770
Is it true?
Did Min Jun really lose his memory?

37
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:23,310
First, Mr. Park is exhibiting signs
of traumatic brain injury...

38
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:26,580
and memory loss
following the hit-and-run.

39
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:36,450
He has retrograde amnesia,
meaning he lost his past memories.

40
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:38,220
To put it simply,

41
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:41,630
his mind has reverted to
when he was around 20 years old.

42
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:49,600
Does that mean he can't remember
anything from after he turned 20?

43
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,010
Yes, that's correct.

44
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,640
How could this happen to my Min Jun?

45
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,180
Oh, no.

46
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:06,220
Then, what about Chloe's condition?

47
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:08,850
Right, how's Chloe?

48
00:04:09,050 --> 00:04:12,620
Chloe's condition is more
psychological than neurological.

49
00:04:12,890 --> 00:04:13,990
Psychological?

50
00:04:18,530 --> 00:04:21,830
She has dissociative amnesia
caused by extreme stress and shock.

51
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:26,500
Simply put,
she doesn't even know who she is.

52
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:31,340
She doesn't even know who she is?

53
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:35,580
So, what happens now?

54
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:39,050
Please give both patients time
and monitor them closely.

55
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:43,020
Forcing them to remember
or giving them too much info...

56
00:04:43,490 --> 00:04:44,890
could backfire.

57
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:47,160
What do we do?

58
00:04:50,460 --> 00:04:51,460
Oh, no.

59
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:03,610
My son is alive,
but I can't even see him...

60
00:05:04,010 --> 00:05:05,580
or hold him.

61
00:05:07,910 --> 00:05:11,280
I should've made Kim Myung Hui
suffer this exact same pain.

62
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,050
For my Hyun Jun's sake,

63
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:18,360
I should've gotten rid of
that punk Park Min Jun for good.

64
00:05:33,340 --> 00:05:34,770
There you go again.

65
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:37,140
Why are you looking at me like that?

66
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:41,050
You had that look when you told us
Park Min Jun was in the hospital.

67
00:05:41,450 --> 00:05:42,810
It's been strange.

68
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,220
I'm not acting any different.

69
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:49,890
You're the one
who seems different, ma'am.

70
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:54,530
You're tense, like you feel guilty
about something.

71
00:05:55,090 --> 00:05:57,960
See? Your words have a bite to them.

72
00:05:58,830 --> 00:06:00,930
You're trying to blame me,
aren't you?

73
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,800
Just like Myung Hui,

74
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,940
do you think I'm responsible
for Min Jun's accident?

75
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,710
Who's to say?

76
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:11,540
Maybe you are, maybe you aren't.

77
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:15,610
Jung Ran!

78
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:21,150
Jung Ran, it's about Park Min Jun.

79
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:23,550
Shut it. I already know.

80
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:25,790
Oh, you do?

81
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:31,360
But I thought amnesia was
just something you see in TV shows.

82
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:32,960
I guess it's a real thing.

83
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,000
And Chloe has it, too.

84
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:40,610
Double amnesia?
Even TV shows don't go that far.

85
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,710
Wait a minute.

86
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:44,840
Amnesia?

87
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:48,610
They both have amnesia?

88
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:59,120
It must be confusing
to have your memory erased.

89
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,330
Yes.

90
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,730
Honestly, I'm a bit...

91
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:04,630
overwhelmed.

92
00:07:07,770 --> 00:07:10,870
Mom's here for you, so don't worry.

93
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:15,710
I'll help you remember
everything you've forgotten.

94
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:20,210
Okay. I feel like I can believe
whatever you tell me.

95
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:23,820
That's right.
Don't try to figure this out alone.

96
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,580
Just ask me anything.

97
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:30,050
Sure. From now on,
I'll only trust what you say.

98
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:46,340
Well, even though
things turned out this way,

99
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:50,110
it's not all bad.

100
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,550
I see things between us
haven't changed at all, Father.

101
00:08:05,990 --> 00:08:06,990
By the way,

102
00:08:07,390 --> 00:08:09,030
who are we to each other?

103
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:10,900
What?

104
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,400
Us?

105
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:15,130
Are you...

106
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:16,800
my girlfriend?

107
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,650
I don't really remember,

108
00:08:27,910 --> 00:08:29,980
but when I think about
my time on campus,

109
00:08:30,580 --> 00:08:33,580
it feels like there was always
someone with long hair with me.

110
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,420
Min Jun, are you okay?

111
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:39,760
What is it?

112
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:47,230
I'm okay. It's just...

113
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:50,130
I just have a bit of a headache.

114
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:55,410
The doctor said forcing memories
will just make things worse.

115
00:08:56,310 --> 00:08:57,380
Take it slow.

116
00:08:57,910 --> 00:09:00,540
Take your time
and let them return naturally, okay?

117
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:02,810
Okay.

118
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:11,290
Min Jun is awake and recovering,

119
00:09:11,890 --> 00:09:15,930
and losing his memory
might actually be for the best.

120
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:17,900
The problem is...

121
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:23,730
Let's have a word.

122
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:31,340
At the warehouse, Chloe and I...

123
00:09:31,410 --> 00:09:33,510
met for business.

124
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:37,520
And you, Ms. Choi,
came there to get your job back.

125
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,820
That's why you made the trip.

126
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:41,920
What?

127
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:45,790
When the police ask about
what happened,

128
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:48,560
don't say anything more
than necessary.

129
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,800
You stick to this story.

130
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:58,770
Even if they investigate
Min Jun's accident,

131
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,670
what happened at the warehouse...

132
00:10:02,570 --> 00:10:03,840
can never come to light.

133
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:07,180
All right.

134
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:09,250
I'll do as you say.

135
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:20,060
So you have no memory
of the accident whatsoever?

136
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:26,860
Excuse me, but is there anyone
who might have a grudge against her?

137
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:31,900
Well...

138
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:36,370
I can't think of anyone
who'd want to hurt her.

139
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:39,640
Since both victims have amnesia...

140
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,050
Let's step outside to discuss this
in more detail.

141
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,790
Chloe is still recovering.

142
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:50,220
- Sure.
- Right, let's step outside.

143
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:03,870
Where are you going?

144
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:07,970
Outside.

145
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:10,880
I just wanted to go
for a walk alone.

146
00:11:28,490 --> 00:11:31,760
You were the one
in my room earlier, right?

147
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,900
I'm sorry,
but I've lost my memories.

148
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:37,900
Did we know each other?

149
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,170
Yes, we knew each other very well.

150
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:48,080
If this is just an act
to try and fool me,

151
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,180
you're going to regret it.

152
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:54,020
Why would you say that?

153
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:57,050
Why would I pretend to have amnesia?

154
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:01,230
Was I a bad person?

155
00:12:05,130 --> 00:12:06,160
Chloe!

156
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,100
What are you doing to Chloe?

157
00:12:10,940 --> 00:12:12,770
What do you think you're doing here?

158
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:17,210
Chloe is my fiancee.

159
00:12:17,810 --> 00:12:19,180
Of course I have to protect her.

160
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,380
Your fiancee?

161
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:25,850
We'll have to talk about that later.

162
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,360
That must've startled you.

163
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:41,670
We just met,
and yet I'm saying I'm your fiance.

164
00:12:41,930 --> 00:12:42,930
Strange, right?

165
00:12:44,540 --> 00:12:45,640
Don't worry.

166
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,400
From now on,

167
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:51,840
I'll protect you.

168
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:54,910
Chloe!

169
00:12:57,950 --> 00:13:02,020
I'll be the one to protect Chloe.
You can go now, Mr. Park.

170
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:05,720
Are you okay?

171
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,590
Right. Let's go.

172
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:19,900
Come on, let's go.

173
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,150
How's the director doing?

174
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,420
He doesn't remember anything
after age 20,

175
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,560
and it doesn't look like
he'll recover anytime soon.

176
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,730
Try not to worry too much.

177
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:50,500
His memory might come back
if you help fill in the gaps.

178
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:53,370
Why don't you step outside
for some fresh air?

179
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:12,060
Don't tell him.

180
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:18,460
Please don't tell Min Jun
about the things he's forgotten.

181
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:22,070
This is none of your business,
Ms. Choi.

182
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:25,340
Min Jun has been through so much.

183
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,570
He was tormented
by Baek Jin Ju's death,

184
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:29,140
and his relationship
with the chairman...

185
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,910
soured because of Temi Bio.

186
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:32,740
There's no need to tell him
all of that.

187
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:37,750
Maybe he'd be happier
starting over from age 20.

188
00:14:39,180 --> 00:14:42,550
Why this sudden concern
for the director's happiness?

189
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:46,990
I'll start over too,
by Min Jun's side.

190
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,160
What did you just say?

191
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:51,300
I knew it.

192
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:54,300
In the end, you were only thinking
about yourself.

193
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:05,810
I know I've done
a lot of things wrong.

194
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:10,850
Because you hated me,
I acted arrogantly out of spite.

195
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:15,120
I was cocky, thinking I only needed
the chairman's approval.

196
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:19,720
But my feelings for Min Jun
are sincere.

197
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:24,230
So that Min Jun and I
can start over,

198
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:26,830
please give us your blessing.

199
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,740
Min Jun truly despised you.

200
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:37,410
Maybe he doesn't remember anymore,
but I do.

201
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:42,380
I will never give you my blessing,
so you can leave.

202
00:15:44,050 --> 00:15:45,650
And don't bother coming
to the hospital again.

203
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:09,810
Who are we to each other?

204
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:10,910
Are you...

205
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,780
my girlfriend?

206
00:16:13,510 --> 00:16:15,610
I don't really remember,

207
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:17,780
but when I think about
my time on campus,

208
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:21,350
it feels like there was always
someone with long hair with me.

209
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:27,160
His girlfriend?
Someone with long hair?

210
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:30,730
He must mean Baek Jin Ju.

211
00:16:42,410 --> 00:16:44,010
Should I try to be more like her?

212
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:45,580
No.

213
00:16:46,140 --> 00:16:48,650
That could trigger
his memories of her.

214
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:52,150
But if I do nothing...

215
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:57,120
This might be my last chance.

216
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:02,390
One, two...

217
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:07,130
I don't care if I'm just
a replacement for Baek Jin Ju.

218
00:17:07,930 --> 00:17:09,770
Before Min Jun gets his memory back,

219
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,200
I have to do whatever it takes.

220
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,550
Amnesia.

221
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:26,650
What am I supposed to do about that?

222
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:29,120
What do you mean,
what should you do?

223
00:17:30,220 --> 00:17:33,360
You should thank Park Min Jun
for surviving.

224
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:38,230
If he hadn't, you'd be a murderer.
Be grateful and repent.

225
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:42,800
Kim Myung Hui should be repenting
for taking Hyun Jun from me.

226
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:46,870
So, is Hyun Jun
still at the hospital?

227
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:51,240
I want to know how Min Jun
and Hyun Jun are doing,

228
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,710
so go over there right now.

229
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:54,780
No. I'm not going.

230
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,120
Now he's against me too.

231
00:18:01,620 --> 00:18:04,560
Why is everyone in this family
so cold to me?

232
00:18:06,490 --> 00:18:09,630
Fine. I'll just go and see
for myself.

233
00:18:10,290 --> 00:18:11,300
Darn.

234
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:30,750
Look at you, alive and well.

235
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:35,120
So, how does it feel to come back
from the dead?

236
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:38,320
Get away from my son!

237
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,290
What do you think you're doing?

238
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:45,430
Is this how you treat someone
who came all this way to visit?

239
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:46,830
A visit?

240
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:50,070
I doubt that. You came here
because you thought...

241
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:51,440
you could hurt my Min Jun again.

242
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:59,180
I can't even stand the sight of you,
so get out.

243
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:01,950
You think I enjoy looking
at either of your faces?

244
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:04,950
You and that brat disgust me.

245
00:19:04,950 --> 00:19:06,920
Watch what you're saying.

246
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:17,060
Please watch what you're saying.

247
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:18,130
Whatever.

248
00:19:18,130 --> 00:19:19,360
She's finished now.

249
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:22,630
Tell me right now! Where is she?

250
00:19:27,670 --> 00:19:29,470
Min Jun!

251
00:19:30,570 --> 00:19:32,080
Over here. Look at me.

252
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:34,880
- Min Jun!
- Min Jun, are you okay?

253
00:19:43,450 --> 00:19:46,620
I'm here for you.
It's okay. Just breathe.

254
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:07,910
So, about Chloe...

255
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:10,980
Is the amnesia for real or not?

256
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:14,720
I've confirmed it again
with her doctor.

257
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:16,520
It seems to be the real deal.

258
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:19,320
The police also questioned her
about the accident,

259
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:22,230
but she couldn't say anything,
claiming she has no memory.

260
00:20:23,190 --> 00:20:24,360
Really?

261
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,630
I suppose if she remembered,

262
00:20:26,830 --> 00:20:30,530
she would've already told the police
I tried to kill her.

263
00:20:31,570 --> 00:20:33,870
Still, we can't let our guard down.

264
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:37,140
Use her amnesia as grounds...

265
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,610
to end her contract
and get rid of her.

266
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,810
Before she talks to the police,

267
00:20:42,580 --> 00:20:44,510
we need to send her back to the US.

268
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,650
Understood, sir.

269
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:48,390
By the way,

270
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,190
what's going on with Min Jun's case?

271
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:53,890
Still no updates
on the hit-and-run driver?

272
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:56,460
With no evidence or leads,

273
00:20:56,460 --> 00:20:58,700
and both victims suffering
from amnesia,

274
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:00,600
the investigation has hit a wall.

275
00:21:01,630 --> 00:21:04,570
Enough with the excuses.
Tell them to find him at all costs!

276
00:21:07,340 --> 00:21:09,670
The punk who hurt my son...

277
00:21:11,210 --> 00:21:13,310
will get no mercy from me.

278
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:21,350
Min Jun,

279
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,490
are you okay?

280
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:25,520
Yes.

281
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:27,560
I'm feeling better now.

282
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:33,630
Thanks to you,
my headache is starting to go away.

283
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:35,470
Thank you.

284
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,840
I'm just glad I could help.

285
00:21:55,390 --> 00:21:59,490
Ma'am, I found someone
to guard the director's room.

286
00:22:01,990 --> 00:22:05,530
I'll be his caregiver and bodyguard.
You don't have to worry.

287
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:36,490
It must've been hard
staying strong in front of Min Jun.

288
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:40,160
It was.

289
00:22:43,830 --> 00:22:45,570
He's lost his memory...

290
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,340
and must be so confused.

291
00:22:49,470 --> 00:22:53,280
I was afraid that if I cried,
it would make things harder for him.

292
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:57,810
You can let it all out here.

293
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:02,890
I honestly thought...

294
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:07,190
I was going to lose Min Jun.

295
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,670
Thinking I was responsible...

296
00:23:16,570 --> 00:23:19,840
How is this your fault?
Oh Jung Ran's to blame.

297
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:23,570
Look at her showing up
at the hospital...

298
00:23:23,570 --> 00:23:24,810
after what she did to him.

299
00:23:25,940 --> 00:23:27,710
That woman is a monster.

300
00:23:29,450 --> 00:23:32,280
I mean, even after Myung Hui died,

301
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:35,450
she came to Dr. Baek's clinic
looking for Min Jun.

302
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:38,220
I think...

303
00:23:38,990 --> 00:23:41,190
my digging into
Oh Jung Ran's past...

304
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:46,100
is what caused her
to go after Min Jun.

305
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:51,640
Because of my revenge,

306
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:54,940
Min Jun almost died,

307
00:23:56,210 --> 00:23:59,210
and now he's lost his memory.

308
00:24:00,910 --> 00:24:02,850
Don't beat yourself up over it.

309
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:05,320
Min Jun is awake now,

310
00:24:07,420 --> 00:24:09,450
and he'll get his memories back.

311
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:14,560
Do you think
he'll ever get them back?

312
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:19,230
He's in so much pain
whenever he tries to remember.

313
00:24:22,470 --> 00:24:23,730
Part of me...

314
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:27,700
almost wishes
he'd never remember anything.

315
00:24:30,770 --> 00:24:32,010
Min Jun...

316
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:35,650
was smiling at Ms. Choi,

317
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:39,020
and I couldn't tell him the truth...

318
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:42,750
about their relationship.

319
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:50,160
It's been so long
since I'd seen him smile...

320
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,700
so peacefully.

321
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:56,070
I just wanted him to be happy,

322
00:24:57,070 --> 00:24:59,700
even if it meant
forgetting everything.

323
00:25:06,410 --> 00:25:07,940
But is that the right thing to do?

324
00:25:12,550 --> 00:25:14,020
I just don't know...

325
00:25:14,820 --> 00:25:16,550
what to do anymore.

326
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:23,430
What do I do? My poor Min Jun.

327
00:25:23,430 --> 00:25:24,530
What do I do?

328
00:25:32,300 --> 00:25:35,270
Park Min Jun has amnesia
from the hit-and-run.

329
00:25:36,370 --> 00:25:39,340
He's gone back to being
a clueless 20-year-old kid.

330
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:42,080
How can we let someone like that
run the company?

331
00:25:43,310 --> 00:25:46,080
The board, executives,
and shareholders must all...

332
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:47,620
pressure the chairman.

333
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:53,190
Tell him to remove Park Min Jun
as director. Got it?

334
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,360
Min Jun,

335
00:25:58,460 --> 00:26:00,930
let's go have some fun with this
once you're discharged.

336
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,070
Sure.

337
00:26:03,430 --> 00:26:04,430
Really?

338
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,740
Yes, that sounds good.

339
00:26:11,910 --> 00:26:13,610
Here, have a nice cold drink.

340
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,350
Right, thank you.

341
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:20,850
It's getting late,
you should probably head out.

342
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:24,420
It's not that late.

343
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:28,890
Min Jun, can I stay a little longer?

344
00:26:29,230 --> 00:26:30,230
Sure.

345
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:32,430
I told you,
you don't have to be so formal.

346
00:26:32,730 --> 00:26:36,900
Sorry. With my amnesia,
it feels like we just met today.

347
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:42,010
Really? Then maybe we should
start over from the beginning...

348
00:26:46,780 --> 00:26:49,580
Hold on. What are you doing here?

349
00:26:49,950 --> 00:26:52,080
Wait. Do you two know each other?

350
00:26:53,150 --> 00:26:56,090
Well, I'm working a second job
as a caregiver.

351
00:26:56,590 --> 00:26:59,520
My shift's almost over,
so I should get going.

352
00:27:06,630 --> 00:27:07,730
What's with you?

353
00:27:09,030 --> 00:27:10,470
Choi Yu Na, what are you doing here?

354
00:27:11,070 --> 00:27:12,070
And on top of that,

355
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:15,110
what's with this get-up?

356
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:18,210
It's obviously because...

357
00:27:19,980 --> 00:27:21,850
Well, Min Jun needs me.

358
00:27:23,010 --> 00:27:26,950
Min Jun got a headache
trying to remember something,

359
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,820
and I was the one who comforted him.

360
00:27:29,490 --> 00:27:32,520
I'm staying by his side
in case it happens again.

361
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,330
You? Taking care of him?

362
00:27:36,860 --> 00:27:38,430
- Is that true?
- Yes.

363
00:27:38,560 --> 00:27:40,700
I had a bad headache earlier.

364
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:44,970
So, you'd better be careful.

365
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:48,610
Watch what you say.
You might give him a headache.

366
00:27:50,070 --> 00:27:51,740
Why don't you leave now?

367
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:54,440
If you stay here any longer,

368
00:27:55,510 --> 00:27:57,450
I might have a lot more to say.

369
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:05,590
You two don't get along, do you?

370
00:28:05,860 --> 00:28:06,860
- We don't.
- We do.

371
00:28:08,490 --> 00:28:09,590
I mean, probably.

372
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:16,670
Right.

373
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,040
Thanks for everything.

374
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:23,940
It was nothing.

375
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:25,940
But are you really okay?

376
00:28:26,780 --> 00:28:27,940
Between the hospital and work...

377
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:32,020
There's no telling
what Oh Jung Ran will do next.

378
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,850
Until Min Jun is out
of the hospital,

379
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:35,720
I should keep a close eye on him.

380
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:38,520
I'll take it from here,
so head home.

381
00:28:39,020 --> 00:28:41,220
- All right. I'm heading out then.
- Okay.

382
00:28:43,690 --> 00:28:44,690
What?

383
00:28:50,430 --> 00:28:52,200
Is Chloe doing any better?

384
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,970
She can't remember a thing.

385
00:28:57,370 --> 00:29:00,310
"Your name is Chloe."
"I'm your dad."

386
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:02,780
I even had to tell her that.

387
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:06,750
For such a brilliant child
to end up like this overnight...

388
00:29:15,530 --> 00:29:16,530
Hello?

389
00:29:17,030 --> 00:29:20,530
What? What do you mean
Chloe isn't in her room?

390
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:23,900
Yes, okay.
I'll look for her right away.

391
00:29:25,940 --> 00:29:28,340
- I'll help him look for her.
- Oh, sure.

392
00:29:29,010 --> 00:29:30,010
Go.

393
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:40,250
Park Hyun Jun, that jerk.

394
00:29:41,850 --> 00:29:44,990
Whatever. At least I stopped him
from saying anything weird.

395
00:29:46,420 --> 00:29:49,730
Park Min Jun held my hand,

396
00:29:50,430 --> 00:29:52,400
smiled, and relied on me.

397
00:29:56,470 --> 00:29:58,970
Dressing up like Baek Jin Ju
actually worked.

398
00:30:00,970 --> 00:30:04,040
I have to take full advantage
of this opportunity.

399
00:30:19,790 --> 00:30:21,090
There's no need to be nervous.

400
00:30:21,690 --> 00:30:24,130
They said Chloe lost her memory too.

401
00:30:26,530 --> 00:30:29,070
Seriously.
Why is she staring at me like that?

402
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:33,200
Could she be faking her amnesia?
Is it a lie?

403
00:30:37,940 --> 00:30:40,940
Excuse me,
why are you staring at me like that?

404
00:30:41,810 --> 00:30:44,780
I've lost my memory.

405
00:30:46,180 --> 00:30:47,250
So?

406
00:30:47,780 --> 00:30:49,790
Do you happen to know me?

407
00:30:52,220 --> 00:30:54,560
No, not at all.

408
00:30:59,230 --> 00:31:00,230
What is this?

409
00:31:03,100 --> 00:31:04,500
What do you think you're doing?

410
00:31:08,070 --> 00:31:09,310
But I feel like...

411
00:31:10,510 --> 00:31:12,080
I recognize you.

412
00:31:14,010 --> 00:31:15,010
Something...

413
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:17,810
is coming back to me.

414
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:19,480
What?

415
00:31:20,650 --> 00:31:21,990
We know each other, don't we?

416
00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:25,860
I...

417
00:31:26,060 --> 00:31:27,420
I told you, I don't.

418
00:31:28,190 --> 00:31:29,730
Yes, we do.

419
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:32,630
I'm so close to remembering.

420
00:31:34,030 --> 00:31:35,030
I remember...

421
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:49,710
Chloe!

422
00:31:50,710 --> 00:31:51,710
Chloe.

423
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,400
Chloe?

424
00:32:52,140 --> 00:32:55,080
(Pearl in Red)

425
00:32:55,650 --> 00:32:57,250
Ms. Kim, there's a huge problem.

426
00:32:57,250 --> 00:32:58,820
Ms. Choi, this is the police.

427
00:32:58,820 --> 00:33:01,020
What the heck did you do?

428
00:33:01,020 --> 00:33:03,950
Announce
Park Min Jun's amnesia publicly.

429
00:33:03,950 --> 00:33:07,120
Use a provocative headline
and plaster it on the front page.

430
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:09,230
The succession war at Adele
has begun.

431
00:33:09,230 --> 00:33:11,960
Oh Jung Ran and I will have
to face each other head-on.

432
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:15,500
I have to take what she has.

433
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:17,700
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
